### 6D. DeviantArt via Browser (ALWAYS LAST)

Run this after all other platform uploads are complete. **Do NOT use `da_upload.py` — the VM cannot reach the DeviantArt API.**

**Check login status:**

Navigate to `https://www.deviantart.com` and take a screenshot. If you see "Join / Log In" in the top-right (not a user avatar), stop and tell the user: *"You need to be logged into DeviantArt in Chrome. Please log in, then let me know."* Wait for confirmation before continuing.

**Navigate to the Sta.sh item:**

Go directly to the Sta.sh URL: `{stash_url_nsfw}`

Scroll below the photo until you see the "Edit or Submit" button (next to "Sell Deviation"). Click it.

**Fill the submission form:**

1. **Title** — Triple-click to select all, then type `{final_title}`
2. **Mature checkbox** — Check it only if `da_nsfw_flag == TRUE`. Leave unchecked if FALSE.
3. **Tags** — Remove all existing tags (click the × on each), then add each keyword from `{final_keywords}` one at a time, pressing Enter after each. Note: multi-word tags are split by spaces on DA — use CamelCase for compound tags (e.g. `streetphotography`, `SoutheastAsia`).
4. **Description** — Click the description field and type `{final_caption}`
5. **Gallery** — Leave as Featured (default) unless the user specifies otherwise

**Pre-submit confirmation:** Take a screenshot of the fully filled form and show it to the user. Ask: *"Ready to publish to DeviantArt?"* Wait for explicit confirmation before clicking Submit.

**After submission:** DeviantArt redirects to the live deviation page. The URL format is `https://www.deviantart.com/flyy1/art/{deviation_id}`. Capture this as `deviation_url`.

If a "Boost for more visibility" dialog appears, click **Maybe Later** to dismiss it.

This is the point at which the Sta.sh item is consumed — it will no longer be accessible at the original Sta.sh URL.

